    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="487" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <head>No. 482.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mantilla</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    Spain in Washington</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">New
                                York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 26, 1878</date>. (Received June
                            27.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of His
                        Catholic Majesty, affected by the most profound feelings, performs the sad
                        duty of communicating to the honorable Secretary of State of the United
                        States, for the information of the President of the Republic and of the
                        government of which he is the head, that he has just received a telegram
                        from the minister of state of His Majesty the <pb facs="0880" n="818" xml:id="pg_818"/> King of Spain, notifying him of the death, at a
                        quarter past twelve o’clock to-day, of Her Majesty the Queen, Doña Maria de
                        las Mercedes de Orleans y Borbon, resulting from a nervous gastric
                        fever.</p>
                <p>Upon this sad occasion the undersigned has the honor of renewing,
                        &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ANTONIO MANTILLA.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
